# Installed by the EinsZweiDrei Claude Kit.
#
# The kit ships shell scripts and an extensionless git hook. These MUST stay LF on
# every platform — a CRLF line ending breaks the `#!/bin/sh` shebang and `bash`/`sh`
# parsing when the repo is checked out on Linux/macOS (e.g. a CI runner or a cloud
# container). Without these rules a Windows checkout would silently corrupt the hooks.
*.sh        text eol=lf
.githooks/* text eol=lf

# claude-audit.py and any other kit Python scripts are run directly; keep them LF too.
*.py        text eol=lf
